{
  "texts": [
    "To further increase the transmission rate, Ma et al. [92] designed a higher order modulation strategy for the multi-carrier FMCW radar by combining the indices of antennas and carrier frequencies.Due to the inherent FH property, FH-MIMO radar enjoys the advantages of high security and strong anti-jamming ability [93,94].",
    "In addition, the communication message can naturally be represented by different FH codes, making FH-MIMO radar a promising candidate for ISAC [95,96].",
    "For example, Hassanien et al. [42] proposed a PM-based information embedding strategy for FH-MIMO radar, which suffered from the challenge of phase discontinuity.",
    "To overcome this problem, Baxter et al. [97] used different FH codes to deliver the communication message.",
    "In addition, various IM-based signaling strategies have been proposed to increase the communication rate, including spatial IM [98], sub-carrier and transmit antenna indices [46], waveform permutation [99], and hybrid IM [47]."
  ]
}